
Serena paused. I'd known her long enough to know what she was doing; she was thinking like a detective. Serena could have her "blonde moments," but she was one of the smartest people I knew. Her dad had taught her well in the art of sleuthing. Me, on the other hand, I was self-taught. "Just meet us at Jasmine's house, okay? We're going to need her tricked-up computers. I'll see you in a few, yeah?"
I nodded, even though I knew she can't see me. "Yeah. See you in a few," I said before hanging up. I took a deep breath. This search for Savannah was not going to be as easy as I thought... especially if these members of the Coterie of Killers kept coming after me.